ring options share on linkedin share on pinterest share on google share on whatsapp share on messenger close jane martinson media business editor janemartinson friday  february   est first published on friday  february   est lucian grainge is sitting crosslegged on his office sofa twiddling his fingers and trying not to sound irritated by questions about the role of big business in the music industry the head of universal music uk  which sells one in four of the records we buy and manages acts from keane to eminem to u  is adamant that universal is not really very commercial at all what makes something corporate i believe our company is the least corporate company in the corporate world he says its built up with a bunch of talented focused intelligent passionate people who like developing music and making it why is that corporate it is a question that could be answered this wednesday night at the annual industry lovein that is the british record industry awards or brits millions of viewers will tune in to watch stars such as franz ferdinand joss stone snow patrol and both bedingfields perform at the th anniversary event many more millions of pounds will be raised for charity largely through corporate tables that dominate the space at the earls court event rather than the few hundred screaming fans likely to dominate television screens at last years event one industry executive described beyoncé as a great product beautifully packaged grainge  and a cochairman of this years event has little time for those who fear the impact of the increasingly huge global record companies on the business the awards are an opportunity for us to enjoy and celebrate british music and celebrate the music business he says to be fair grainge and the british music industry itself have something to celebrate this year the industry finds itself in positive sales territory for the first time in years with a  increase in album sales universals sales rose  in the uk last year as the market leader managed to increase its share of the albums and singles market to more than  it had three albums in the top  including the top two by scissor sisters and keane these two acts are also indicative of what has been described as a resurgent british music industry scissors an american band were signed in the uk four of the top five albums were by british acts last year four of whom were previously unknown acts peter jamieson chairman of the trade body the british phonographic industry says he cant remember the last time the charts were not dominated by foreigners the success last year earned grainge and his team a special mention in last weeks results from its giant parent company vivendi universal they were praised for an exceptional year for breaking new artists it isnt long in the conversation with grainge before talk turns to which new acts could help make this year as good as last any discomfort disappears and like an ageing rock star coming into a packed auditorium he jumps up from the sofa and runs over to his stereo system shouting thats the best bit before we know where we are he has turned up the volume on a demo disc and launched into a story about the next big thing the story starts when someone who knew grainge  years ago rang and said hed found a new talent he brings this guy in and i flip says grainge i do it on the spot i call the head of mercury one of universals record labels and i say if you like this as much as i like it weve got a deal thats the gift this guy bobby kray his name is kray he looks like someone from jamiroquai yet has the voice of an angel he was a choir boy at st pauls or somewhere when he was  or something  hes the machinegun patter stalls momentarily hes stunning but how can he tell that this new act will sell grainge who is wearing a dark suit over an opennecked shirt revealing a mat of dark chest hair leans over and says i can smell it after  or  years its a smell by this point he is rifling through the stack of discs and tapes on his desk we sit listening to at least five different yettobe launched acts grainge a stocky man hums nods and stamps along to the entire show he knows the pauses speaks up at the bits that need a little bit more work and points out the choruses that will work how does this middleaged man who grew up in north london loving the clash and the sex pistols know what it takes for a hiphop pop or soul song to work at this question he smiles and says softly thats the gift i was a publisher for the first  years of my career i understand songs its very very difficult to define i can definitely smell it i can feel it in my fingertips his ability to pick artists who work across a range of styles does mark grainge out but then it also marks out universal which produced half of the classical albums released last year as well as busted his gift is allied to his business skills in describing the first time he heard one new act the bravery he says it was the best thing id heard i absolutely loved it it ticked every box  radio tv press merchandise the look the trend yet it is impossible not to feel that grainge really does love music and not just because the words i love this business and i absolutely love this act like a refrain to his speech he left school at  after walking out of an alevel exam to attend a meeting in which he helped to negotiate his first record deal he earned £ and knew he had crossed a divide i felt comfortable and normal around musicians and artists and managers i liked the social scene and loved the music i was absolutely obsessed with it his life today  regular dinners with sir elton john and a big house near richmond southwest london  is a far cry from his early days when his father owned a television and radio shop with a carousel of s in it and the young lucian managed a band at school yet he maintains a link to what people really want he says by taking some of his senior managers to local high streets youre going to think im mad but what i do with my senior people is go and observe people he says i love going to coventry harrow west bromwich thats where i walk into stores and get a sense of what people are wearing and what they want theres an awful lot of data in the record business  but to actually see these people and get a sense of demographics he tails off he is scathing of critics of realitytv programmes such as pop idol or fame academy describing them simply as family entertainment he adds why not let people enjoy themselves why must we judge people all the time his first proper job was plugging songs trying to get radio stations to play his companys music within five years he had moved to a record label and was director of ar  artist and repertoire  which combines spotting talent with developing it grainge believes his background and that of his top team differentiates universal from its main competitors which are now reduced to three after sony and bmg agreed to merge last year explaining the difference grainge says i am from an ar background all those other guys are from marketing jamieson at the bpi who is cochair of the brits says grainge is a oneoff  in what can appear a cutthroat music business he can be both harsh and gentle both businessman and music devotee his boss doug morris chairman of universal music group has said of him he is so deceptive with that little kind face and those little glasses behind them he is actually a killer shark despite his obvious love of the industry grainge is reluctant to name the music he listens to for pleasure he begins by saying he cant listen to music at home as his youngest children who are five and  overtake the system so what does he listen to in the car alone i love listening to the scissors in the car they had the numberone biggest most successful selling album last year how about music he wasnt necessarily involved in the buzz of listening to one of the artists we have been involved with and which has sold millions is very therapeutic he smiles but is there any music he just really loves finally he says presley led zeppelin the clash the sex pistols but he admits he could never name a truly favourite band especially not a stillperforming one for fear of the people who would feel slighted when youre in this business and particularly when youve been in this business since you were  like i have theres no difference between the personal and business he says previous interviews have made much of the running machine unplugged and unloved at the back of grainges office but he seems to use up plenty of energy bouncing around the room and talking about work i love it i am stimulated by it the only time that the phone doesnt ring and the blackberry doesnt work is over christmas but thats because no one else is working this wednesday grainge is likely to be in his element his frontrow table at the brits will be graced by some of universals top international executives as well as the singer amy winehouse a million miles away from all those record buyers in the midlands yet when he hears that my mum is an il divo fan he insists that i take her a new tape from a yettobe released crooner patrizio buanne shes a big market your mum give her this and tell me what she thinks tell me as soon as possible before next week really i mean it and i think he really does the cv born north london education left school at  career  joined april musiccbs as a song plugger promoted to head of the creative department  director of rca music publishing  director of ar at mca records  set up polygram music publishing  joined polydor as general manager of ar and business affairs  promoted to managing director  promoted to deputy chairman of universal music uk  promoted to chairman and chief executive director of the british phonographic industry and cochairman of the brits committee family married with three children keen arsenal fan topics media business music industry lucian grainge share on facebook share on twitter share via email share on linkedin share on pinterest share on google share on whatsapp share on messenger reuse this content most viewed lucian grainge  wikipedia lucian grainge from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search sir lucian grainge birth name lucian charles grainge born   february  age  london england occupations chairman  chief executive officer universal music group years active –present labels universal music group sir lucian charles grainge cbe born  february  is the chairman and chief executive officer of universal music group over the course of his career he has been instrumental in the careers of artists such as amy winehouse abba eurythmics rihanna sam smith take that psychedelic furs the rolling stones sting u jamie cullum and andrea bocelli grainge has worked in the music business for his entire career in   and  he topped billboard magazine’s “power ” list as the most powerful person in the music business the only person to ever hold that distinction three times and the first to earn that position for consecutive years irving azoff called him the great hope for the music business and jimmy iovine commented that grainge is working to restore a spirit of risktaking and innovation by being willing and open to entrepreneurship and that kind of thing the record industry has gotten depleted of in an interview with grainge billboard wrote “if “power” means moving markets or greenlighting massive spends universal music group chairman lucian grainge demonstrated a staggering penchant for it when umg completed its  billion acquisition of emi’s recordedmusic assets in september  grainge is a fierce and tireless advocate for the recordedmusic business in  cnet wrote that “grainge is positioning universal to lead the pack” of major labels in their embracing of new digital opportunities a  frontpage la times profile of grainge said that if anyone can save the music business it might be grainge in  billboard wrote “in the age of spotify youtube and shazam grainge is positioned to tackle his business overriding priority win fair compensation for artists and take full ownership of content that other parties have been profiting from” contents  early life and career  universal music group  personal life  industry honours and other achievements  references  external links early life and careeredit lucian grainge grew up in north london grainge worked his way up in the london music scene after leaving queen elizabeths grammar school for boys at the age of  when he began working as a runner at a talent scout company called mpc after calling several record label heads from the music week directory he got through to maurice oberstein the chairman of cbc records who hired him for publishing company april musics ar department his first signing was the psychedelic furs in  he became the director of rca music publishing two years later he became an ar director for mca records he set up polygram music publishing in  and joined polydor as gm of ar and business affairs in  he was promoted to managing director of polydor in  and had success with acts including boyzone and the lighthouse family since becoming chairman and chief executive of universal music in  grainge has overseen a strategy to increase universals digital distribution international expansion and market leadership in both recorded music and publishing bestselling artists signed to universal music in recent years have included rihanna lady gaga jessie j amy winehouse carly rae jepsen and maroon  universal music groupedit grainge became the chairman of the uk division of the universal music group and later became chairman of universal music group international in  he served in this position until  on  january  he became ceo of the universal music group and later became chairman on  march  he succeeded doug morris who served as chairman and ceo since  grainge has been influential in universal music groups international digital expansion by pioneering distribution models with a wide range of technology partners including apple spotify bskyb rdio virgin media vodafone and  entertainment he recently established the licensed music service onestop china with baidu as well as a deal with bin to break taiwanese acts on the mainland there is also an agreement in place with reliance to start indias first mobile music service grainge also helped arrange the partnership between bravado universal musics entertainment merchandising division and tommy hilfiger and oversaw expansion for flagship classical labels deutsche grammophon and decca classics he also put together the global strategic partnership with entertainment company live nation within his first year as chairman  ceo of universal he led the company in acquiring emis recorded music operations in doing so he argued that selling to universal was the only way to make emi better and thus lift the entire industry he made the revitalisation of former emi labels such as capitol records and virgin records a key part of his strategy as a result of the emi acquisition grainge will go down as the master architect of what is likely to be the last big deal in the music business in the emi deal umg acquired the beatles catalogue umgs merchandising division bravado subsequently secured north american merchandising for the band umg is now creating a unified marketing strategy for the music and associated products of the most influential and beloved band in the history of music the wisdom of the acquisition was further illustrated by the quick success of the revitalized capitol music group in  capitol earned all the major grammy awards for the year with sam smith receiving best new artist record of the year and song of the year awards and beck winning album of the year in  grainge partnered with russell simmons brian robbins and steve rifkind to create all def music the first major labelaffiliated music company created specifically to sign develop and promote artists on youtube russell simmons called grainge the most innovative of music executives umg partnered with samsung in the spring of  to launch a music service in africa called the kleek featuring the companys international catalogue as well as local artists under grainges leadership umg has broken a string of records becoming the first company in the us to have nine of the top  songs on the digital charts according to soundscan and weeks later becoming the first company to hold all  of the top  spots on the billboard hot  chart according to an industry insider umgs enterprise value in  years stands to be closing in on  billion in  grainge was featured in a documentary film that depicts the life and death of late british singer amy winehouse entitled amy which was released theatrically in july in  vivendi announced that grainge agreed to extend his tenure as umg’s chairman and ceo until at least  stating he was key to its strategy under his leadership umg experienced growth in annual revenue digital recorded music revenue and ebitda personal lifeedit in january  grainge married his first wife attorney samantha berg that november she experienced complications while giving birth to their son elliot and fell into a coma from which she never recovered she died in england in  in  grainge married his second wife caroline their daughter alice was born in  in november  grainge and his wife reportedly paid  million usd for a house in pacific palisades they had previously leased a brentwood home from the owner of rhino entertainment his older brother was nigel grainge the founder of ensign records industry honours and other achievementsedit in  grainge was honoured with the prestigious music industry trusts’ award which recognises the world’s most influential and successful executives in music members of u presented him with the award and other acts he was associated with like take that performed grainge was appointed commander of the order of the british empire cbe in the  new year honours for services to the creative industries in  uk prime minister david cameron appointed him as a british business ambassador he was knighted in the  birthday honours for services to british business and inward investment he was inaugurated to appointment to the order of the british empire and knight bachelor by prince william on november   grainge is a trustee of the american friends of the royal foundation of the duke and duchess of cambridge and prince harry httpwwwroyalfoundationcomcontactus in  he received the humanitarian award from the foundation for ethnic understanding that same year umg was honoured with a sagaftra american scene award recognising the companys commitment to diversity as exemplified by its entire catalog and roster of artists in  he was awarded the presidents merit award icon award by the recording academy in recognition of his significant contributions to the music industry in  he will receive the spirit of life award from the city of hope recognizing his outstanding achievements in business and his dedication to philanthropic causes grainge serves on the boards of lionsgate and northeastern university in october  variety presented grainge with its  empowerment award for overseeing a noticeable shift in the demographics of the industry leader’s csuites” with women occupying some of the highest executive positions at universal music group in may  the cannes lions international festival of creativity announced that grainge would be honored as the  media person of the year he is the first music executive to be recognized since the award was launched in  he was awarded an honorary doctorate of music by the berklee college of music in may  and an honorary doctorate of global commerce by northeastern university in may of  referencesedit  debretts  the trusted source on british social skills etiquette and styledebretts debrettscom retrieved    pregrammy gala to honor lucian grainge grammycom   a b c lucian grainge the  billboard power  billboard   lucian grainge tops billboards  power  list fmqb  